<h2> Session #3: </h2>
</p>Upon their arrival at Baldom the party is immediatly chained by the rest of the wizards of Baldom and their ratfolk slave soldiers, and thrown into a dungeon. Due to their overconfidence -and definetely not due to the gm's forgetfulness- the party's captors didn't bother to unarm or search them. George uses his bunny familiar to steal the keys their and cell.<p>
</p>After freeing themselves and Thaddeus, the players start to make their escape, with Thaddeus pretending to be a rat soldier of the wizards transporting them as prisoners. This way the party manages to escape the wizards' attention, steal supplies and exit the fortress where they were held prisoners.<p>
</p>Into the ruined city the player's with the help of Thaddeus manage to track the wizard down at a nearby tavern. Thaddeus uses his psychic abilities to make some of the patrons attack the wizard in order to distract him, as George steals the relic from him and Thanasis poisons his wine, immediatly thereafter the party teleports back to Greenhill, where a feast is held celebrating them as local heroes. <p>
